    "department": "Workplace and Real Estate",
    "description": "About ALSO.\n\nWe’re ALSO, an electric mobility company originally conceived as a part of Rivian. We’re a passionate team of builders, dreamers, doers and innovators, focused on creating entirely new (not to mention, innovative and delightful) vertically integrated, small EVs designed to meet the global mobility challenges of today and tomorrow. Our mission is to inspire everyone to ride ALSO—replacing many local car, truck and SUV miles with ones on vehicles that are more affordable, more enjoyable and 10-50x more efficient.\n\nALSO's Real Estate and Workplace Services team is looking for a Environmental Health, Safety \u0026 Security (EHS\u0026S) Manager to own and lead enterprise-level EHS programs while playing a key role in physical security, access control systems, and the development of Security Operations Center (SOC) protocols who will report to the Director of Real Estate and Workplace Services. This is a hands-on, highly autonomous position requiring deep technical expertise, strong judgment, and the ability to operate independently across our office, R\u0026D, commercial/retail, field deployments, and sites worldwide. This role is required to be onsite 5 days a week during business hours with some domestic and international travel as needed.\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\nEHS Program Ownership \u0026 Leadership\n\n - Own the design, implementation, and continuous improvement of company-wide EHS programs aligned with OSHA (1910/1926), EPA, NFPA, and applicable global regulations\n\n - Establish scalable EHS frameworks that support rapid growth, international expansion, and field deployments\n\n - Conduct audits, inspections, and risk assessments across offices, labs, facilities, and commercial/retail sites\n\n - Lead incident investigations using a systems-based, no-blame approach; ensure timely corrective and preventative actions\n\n - Develop and enforce site-specific safety plans including lockout/tagout, fall protection, hot work, equipment safety, hazardous material handling, and SOW/contractor management\n\n - Partner with various departments to report and resolve worker’s comp, workplace safety, compliance, and risk related claims\n\n - Serve as the primary EHS authority during regulatory inspections and external audits with local departments\n\nSecurity \u0026 Emergency Management\n\n - Own and evolve physical security and site access control standards and protocols, including badging and visitor management systems\n\n - Partner with Security, Facilities, and IT to help design and operationalize Security Operations Center (SOC) procedures, escalation paths, and incident response playbooks\n\n - Integrate EHS and security risk management into a unified emergency response and crisis management framework\n\n - Develop, test, and maintain emergency response, business continuity, and disaster preparedness plans\n\n - Act as incident lead during safety or security events, coordinating with internal stakeholders and external emergency responders\n\n - Cross-Functional \u0026 Field Engagement\n\n - Embed EHS and security requirements into lab design, site buildouts, equipment installation, and global customer deployments\n\n - Train and influence employees, contractors, and partners through formal training, field engagement, and leadership coaching\n\n - Act as a trusted advisor to Engineering, Operations, Facilities, and Leadership on safety and security risk decisions\n\n - Drive a preventative, proactive, ownership-based safety and security culture across the organization\n\nWhat You Will Bring\n\n - Bachelor’s degree in Environmental Health \u0026 Safety, Engineering, Industrial Hygiene, Environmental Science, or related fields\n\n - 7+ years of progressive EHS experience, with demonstrated ownership of programs in R\u0026D, construction, EV, robotics, or field-deployed environments\n\n - Strong command of OSHA, EPA, NFPA, and incident investigation methodologies\n\n - Proven ability to operate independently, set priorities, and execute without day-to-day oversight\n\n - Experience with physical security systems, access controls, or security operations strongly preferred\n\n - Excellent communication skills with the ability to influence across functions and levels\n\n - Willingness to travel domestically and internationally as needed\n\nPreferred Certifications\n\n - OSHA 30-Hour (Construction or General Industry)\n\n - CSP, ASP, CHST, or equivalent\n\n - First Aid / CPR, HAZWOPER\n\nThe salary for this position ranges from $140,000 -$170,000 depending on experience and qualifications.\n\nWhy ALSO.\n\nWe’re passionate about helping the world find a better way to get there—wherever it is you’re headed.\n\nWe’re located in the heart of Silicon Valley and have brought together a world-class team from some of the biggest brands in the technology, automotive, cycling, outdoor recreation and retail spaces. \n\nTogether we’re working hands-on to imagine, design and build an entirely new solution to a global set of transportation challenges. \n\nPerks and Benefits\n\n - Robust health coverage. Excellent health, dental and vision insurance covered up to 100% by ALSO with FSA \u0026 HSA options.\n\n - One Medical membership and dedicated insurance advocates.\n\n - Rich fertility and family building benefits with Progyny.\n\n - Flexible time off. \n\n - 401(k) match.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
